<subSubSection pageId="146" pageNumber="147" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
Distinctive because of the pilose indumentum with spreading hairs combined with the lanceolate to ovate stem leaves but very close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schrenk, Enum. Pl. Nov. [F. E. L. Fischer &amp; C. A. Meyer] 1: 19. 1841. (Fischer and Meyer" authorityYear="1841" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus subsericeus" order="Solanales" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subsericeus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Convolvulus subsericeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss. &amp; Buhse, Nouv. Mem. Soc. Imp. Naturalises Moscou 12: 148. 1860. (Boissier and Buhse" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus eremophilus" order="Solanales" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eremophilus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Convolvulus eremophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From the latter it is best distinguish by the less rigid, less flexuouse branches arising at around 60° from the stem as well as the broader leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
Specimens intermediate between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regel &amp; Schmalh., Trudy Imp. S. - Petersburgsk. Bot. Sada 6: 338. 1879. (Regel" authorityYear="1879" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus divaricatus" order="Solanales" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divaricatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Convolvulus divaricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss. &amp; Buhse, Nouv. Mem. Soc. Imp. Naturalises Moscou 12: 148. 1860. (Boissier and Buhse" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus eremophilus" order="Solanales" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eremophilus">Convolvulus eremophilus</taxonomicName>
exist (
<bibRefCitation author="Grigoriev, C" journalOrPublisher="USSR Scientific Academy, Moscow and Leningrad" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" pagination="1 - 37" refId="B138" refString="Grigoriev, C, 1953. Flora USSR volume 19: Tubiflorae. USSR Scientific Academy, Moscow and Leningrad: 1 - 37" title="Flora USSR volume 19: Tubiflorae" year="1953">Grigoriev 1953</bibRefCitation>
: 19) and have been called 
<taxonomicName authorityName="V. Petrov" authorityYear="1935" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus michelsonii" order="Solanales" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="michelsonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Convolvulus michelsonii</emphasis>
